description:
Our client is a leading European manufacturer of frozen doughs, selling to food services channels and retail bake-off.










 We are looking for an experienced Key Account Manager Sweden to support the growth of professional Foodservice, Retail & Artisanal Bakery business.










 As Key Account Manager Sweden your objective is to develop the sales in Sweden. You take care of the company’s strategy and manage existing accounts as well as seek new business opportunities within and outside the existing customer and product portfolio.










**Your main responsibilities are:** 










 1. To be an entrepreneurial Business Developer:




 · Market & customer data analysis




 · Set out the vision and growth journey for the different channels (Foodservice, Retail & Artisanal Bakery) for the coming years, and take the ownership on the delivery of results;










 2. To be a Key Account Manager:




 · Putting customer needs at the first place to support grow pace of customers;




 · Build and execute the channel business plan and the account;




 · Build customer relationships with strategic accounts in your area (Sweden);




 · Developing long term profitable volume growth;










 3. To be part of the team:




 · Reporting to the Commercial Manager Nordics based in Belgium;




 · Interact frequently with Customer Service and Finance;




 · Fulfil the admin tasks in a consequent way and apply good management of investments and costs.










**Are you the one we’re looking for?** 










 About you










 · You combine ambition and passion for results with forward looking;




 · Own interpersonal sensitivity & empathy,




 · Eager to learn, to develop and to be developed;




 · Embrace and live our corporate values;




 · You are a food lover and/or passionate about food.










 ... And your experiences










 · You own a degree in Economics, Business, Marketing, or a related field;




 · You have at least 5 years of successful commercial experience in FMCG, and preferably expertise in the Swedish professional area (Foodservice);




 · Own analytical skills and problem solving mindset;




 · Experienced in account planning and negotiation skills;




 · Relevant IT skills: Mainly Office but also familiar to work with CRM-tools;




 · You can fluently express yourself in Swedish and English










**What’s in for you?** 










 · You will join our big little family: Our associates are the beating heart of our company – they bring the flavour to our organisation. We cherish each member, prioritising their well-being and supporting their professional journey. As a global family business, we foster a human-centric approach where everyone feels welcome and valued.




 · We value you as a person: We value each one of our associates and recognise their unique contributions to team successes. We place great importance in giving our associates the freedom to shape their own professional journey. You will have flexible working hours.




 · We care about your future, and we support your professional journey: We believe in the power of our associates and the value of their actions and support their career aspirations by offering internal mobility and promotional opportunities. We embrace individual ambitions and encourage our associates to create a successful professional journey and entrust them to take ownership. We encourage that our associates follow different trainings, made available via our Academy portal.




 · We make products for you to love: We are a team of passionate food enthusiasts. In our mission to shape a tasty future we strive to create a wide range of food solutions that connects people, cultures and traditions.
